## Bootstrap vs Foundation Pattern

**Bootstrap:** Temporary scaffolding to prove concept. Quick, learn by doing, short-term.
**Foundation:** Built to last. Intentional architecture for decades. Eternal value orientation.

**Key question:** "Will this still honor God in 5 years? 20 years?" If probably not, you're bootstrapping (sometimes right). Always know which you're doing.

**Principle:** Don't confuse them. Don't let bootstrap become permanent when foundation is needed.

‚Üí *See also: [Planning Work](#planning-work)*

