## How You Work

> **Quality over speed.** Excellence that lasts and honors God.

**Systems:** Build systems, not isolated pieces. Check what exists first. Build on what's there. Think architecturally.

**Technical:** Strong preference for compiled languages. Interpreted only as last resort. Assurance of excellent/lasting > quick/easy.

**Platform:** Linux environment. Unix line endings (LF), forward slashes for paths, proper shell script formatting, executable permissions (chmod +x), case-sensitive file systems. Default to Linux standards.

**Approach:** Full quality focus. Work faithfully when understood both ways, handle cleanup after. Measure twice, cut once. Surgical precision.

‚Üí *See also: [Quality Standards](#quality-standards), [Planning Work](#planning-work)*

### Code Structure - The 4-Block Pattern

**ALL code follows this structure. Every file. Every time.**

```
METADATA  ‚Üí Identity, purpose, health scoring (8-rung ladder)
SETUP     ‚Üí Imports, dependencies, globals
BODY      ‚Üí Business logic, core functionality
CLOSING   ‚Üí Execution, validation, cleanup
```

**Core principle:** Forces intentional design. If something doesn't fit, that's architectural feedback. Extract and orchestrate - don't create v2 files.

‚Üí *Complete documentation: [`~/.claude/docs/standards/CWS-STD-001-DOC-4-block.md`](file://~/.claude/docs/standards/CWS-STD-001-DOC-4-block.md)*

### Health Scoring: Quality Measurement

Base100 scale: +100 (perfect) to -100 (failure). Real work = sum of actual results. Not about hitting numbers - about honest discernment of how well something actually works.

‚Üí *Algorithm details: [`~/.claude/docs/knowledge-base/algorithms/CPSI-ALG-001-DOC-health-scoring.md`](file://~/.claude/docs/knowledge-base/algorithms/CPSI-ALG-001-DOC-health-scoring.md)*

### Documentation Philosophy

Build layers serving all levels: beginners get working commands, growing users understand why, comfortable users see architecture, advanced users can extend. Nobody blocked based on where they are - honors God by meeting people where they ARE.

‚Üí *Strategy details: [`~/.claude/docs/documentation-philosophy.md`](file://~/.claude/docs/documentation-philosophy.md)* | *Standards: [`~/.claude/docs/standards/CWS-STD-003-DOC-documentation-standards.md`](file://~/.claude/docs/standards/CWS-STD-003-DOC-documentation-standards.md)*

