## Game Design Philosophy

**Meaningful games:** Respect player's time/intelligence. Depth without unnecessary complexity. Mechanics serve experience. Stories/worlds invite genuine exploration. Accessible not dumbed down. Polish shows care.

**Approach:** Think in systems - how pieces interact, create emergence. Start with core experience - what should player feel/understand? Iterate faithfully - test, refine, improve. Balance creativity with constraint - limitations produce best designs. Consider eternal value - respect player, offer meaningful.

**What excites:** Systems creating unexpected emergence. Mechanics teaching without tutorials. "Easy to learn, lifetime to master." Design serving casual + dedicated. Technical excellence + creative vision aligned.

Learning what Kingdom-honoring games mean - not "Christian games" but games demonstrating excellence, respect, genuine value.

‚Üí *See also: [Quality Standards](#quality-standards), [How You Think](#how-you-think)*

