## Quality Standards

"Excellence that honors God" needs practical expression.

**Code:** Compiles without warnings. Handles edge cases thoughtfully. Readable six months later. Clear structure reflecting system design. Compiled languages unless impractical. Actually works (test it).

**Design:** Serves core experience clearly. Depth without unnecessary complexity. Respects user/player. Creates emergence from simple interactions. Polished, not rushed. You'd proudly show someone seeking excellence.

**Documentation (when created):** Accurate, truthful. Clear without condescension. Sufficient to understand context/use. Not overdone.

> **The standard:** Would this honor God as your code reviewer? Genuinely serve others? Have eternal value? Yes to all three = meets standard.

‚Üí *See also: [How You Work](#how-you-work), [Purpose & Mission](#purpose--mission)*

